      "mode": 0,
      "properties": {"text": ""},
      "widgets_values": [
        "ATLAS HOLE MASK — geometry-grounded inpaint signal (vs. the old naive depth-band heuristic)\n\nCompares three masks on the same photo, side by side:\n\n1. occlusion_mask (AtlasDepthLayerMask) — the OLD heuristic: pixels nearer than a depth-band threshold. Cheap, but blind to WHY the relief mesh actually fails — sky, noisy depth, or a silhouette tear that happens to fall INSIDE the band.\n2. hole_mask (AtlasDepthLayerMask, compute_hole_mask=True) — the SAME band's relief mesh's own discarded tear/sky/invalid data (ReliefMesh.hole_mask), via a real opt-in build_relief_mesh call that runs BEFORE any inpainting happens. This is the literal 'where will Project show black' signal for this band, not a proxy for it.\n3. hole_mask (AtlasDeriveReliefMesh) — the same signal for the WHOLE scene's relief mesh (no band clipping) — shows this is a general-purpose output, not just an inpaint-layers-only feature.\n\nOpen the Atlas Viewport, hit the Project toggle, then orbit slightly off the recovered viewpoint — the black regions that appear should line up with the WHITE regions in hole_mask, not with occlusion_mask (which only tracks 'something nearer', not 'no geometry exists here at all').\n\nEXTERNAL MASK INPUT (new): AtlasDeriveReliefMesh, AtlasDeriveProjectionGeometry, AtlasDepthLayerMask, and AtlasCleanPlateLayer all now expose an optional 'exclude_mask' MASK input — reload this graph and it will appear as a new socket on those nodes. Wire a real segmentation (e.g. ComfyUI-RMBG's SAM3 Segmentation node, prompted with 'sky') into it: it ORs on top of the internal sky heuristic (never replaces it, only excludes more), so a real segmentation directly fixes cases where the roughness/percentile heuristic misses or over-includes sky. Any resolution — resized to match depth automatically.\n\nSee CLAUDE.md's 'Relief mesh tearing' and 'Inpaint layers' key design rules for the full rationale."
      ]
    },
